            <p>The key to effective packaging is to choose a style that aligns with your product’s needs and enhances the user experience. For example, gable boxes offer convenience, making them great for customers who need to carry items easily. Meanwhile, window die-cut boxes give customers a sneak peek at the product, increasing the likelihood of a purchase.</p>
